body:
I've tested the PR again. 
I found a minor issue with the alternative arguments.
input: `--input abc --p 12`,
code:

``` java
RequiredParameters rq = new RequiredParameters();
        rq.add("input");
        rq.add(new Option("parallelism").alt("p").defaultValue("1").type(OptionType.INTEGER));
        ParameterTool pt = ParameterTool.fromArgs(args);
        rq.applyTo(pt);

        String in = pt.get("input");
        System.out.println("In = "+in + " parallelism = "+pt.getInt("parallelism") + " p="+pt.getInt("p"));

        System.exit(0);
```

error 

```
Exception in thread "main" java.lang.RuntimeException: No data for required key 'p'
    at org.apache.flink.api.java.utils.ParameterTool.getRequired(ParameterTool.java:236)
    at org.apache.flink.api.java.utils.ParameterTool.getInt(ParameterTool.java:272)
    at org.apache.flink.examples.java.wordcount.WordCount.main(WordCount.java:69)
```

I think we need to set the (default) value for the long and the short variant.
